observations.recommendation:
require the Municipal Accountant to drop from the PPE accounts the properties costing less than ₽15,000.00;
require the Property Custodian to replace the existing Property Acknowledgement Receipt (PAR) issued to the end users with the Inventory Custodian Slip (ICS); and
henceforth, record all properties costing less than ₽15,000.00 as inventory upon acquisition and expense upon issuance of the ICS.

We have recommended and management agreed to require the Accounting Office to:

draw the appropriate entries to correct the misclassification of PPE accounts and corresponding depreciation;


segregate the cost of local road networks, maintain separate SLs for the road sub-components, determine the appropriate estimated useful life and compute the depreciation of each sub-components;
exclude the infrastructure assets from the provision of residual value pursuant to Section 262(h) of GAM for LGUs and Section IV(14) of COA Circular No. 2015-008; and

draw the appropriate entries to adjust the erroneous depreciation of infrastructure assets due to provision of residual value.

We have recommended and management agreed to require the Accounting Office to:

record the liquidated damages as Miscellaneous Income which shall be used only through an appropriation;


submit justification and stop using the liquidated damages for the payment of BAC Members’ honoraria.

