We have recommended that management:
 Require the GAD Focal Point to administer the HGDG test on the LGU’s GAD PPAs in the preparation of Accomplishment Report, as basis for determining the actual expenditure that can be attributed to the GAD Budget;
 Administer the HGDG test on the PPAs for CY 2017, the results of which shall be the basis in estimating the cost of gender mainstreaming and GAD Budget;
 If and when necessary, conduct a training program on the HGDG for the incoming year and seek assistance of a gender analysis expert in the use of/and administration of the HGDG; and
 Expedite the implementation of GAD PPAs to accelerate gender mainstreaming in the MLGU operations.

We have recommended that Management:
 Follow up the approval of the 10-year Solid Waste Management Plan;
 Implement strictly the Plan, if approved;
 Conduct information and educational campaign on Solid Waste Management in the barangays and schools, particularly on recycling and segregation of waste at source;
 Require the establishment of Materials Recovery Facilities in all the barangays; and
 Strictly comply with the other provisions of RA No. 9003.

We have recommended that Management:
 Require the Municipal Engineer and his staff to work and exert extra efforts to hasten the implementation and completion of all projects to eliminate all backlog by the end of CY 2017;
 Consider the quantity and nature of development projects being proposed for inclusion in the budget, so that these are proportionate to the capacity of manpower resources of the Municipal Engineering Office;
 Advise the Municipal Development Council through the Municipal Planning and Development Coordinator to evaluate the technical viability and impact of proposed development projects, before these are being requested for appropriation to avoid realignments.

We have recommended that the Local Chief Executive:
 Instruct the Department Heads to follow the proper procedures in budgeting and refrain from preparing and proposing bloated budgets;
 Instruct the Department Heads to submit budgets that are realizable and commensurate to the Department programs, projects and activities (PPAs) that are realizable planned to be implemented in the ensuing year;
 Require the Department Heads to maximize the utilization of their budget by timely implementing the PPAs as planned to avoid the reversion of funds; and
 Seek the advice and assistance lf the Local Finance Committee (LFC) in the preparation of a realistic and attainable budget for the municipality.

