We have recommended that management:
 a) follow up the approval of the 10-year Solid Waste Management Plan;
 b) implement strictly the Plan, if approved;
 c) conduct information and educational campaign on Solid Waste Management and monitor compliance;
 d) require the establishment of Materials Recovery Facilities in all the barangays: and
 e) strictly comply with the other provisions of RA No. 9003.

We have recommended that Management:
 a) Require the Municipal Engineer and his staff to work and exert extra efforts to hasten the implementation and completion of all projects to eliminate all backlog by the end of CY 2017;
 b) consider the quantity and nature of development projects being proposed for inclusion in the budget, so that these are proportionate to the capacity of manpower resources of the Municipal Engineering Office;
 c) advice the Municipal Development Council through the Municipal Planning and Development Coordinator to evaluate the technical viability and impact of proposed development projects, before these are being requested for appropriation to avoid realignments;

We have recommended that the Local Chief Executive-
 Ensure that all executive officials of the municipality faithfully discharge their duties and functions as provided in the Local Government Code to avoid incurrence of overdrafts and insufficiency of funds;
 Collect immediately the bank charges of P112,200.00 from persons responsible and deposit it back to its depository bank;
 Instruct the Municipal Accountant to install strong internal control measures on cash, maintain adequate records to monitor cash in bank, issue Accountant’s Advice of Local Check Disbursement only if funds are sufficient and coordinate regularly with the Municipal Treasurer regarding the MLGU’s finances; and
 Instruct the Municipal Treasurer to diligently perform her duties, update her cashbooks daily and reconcile these with the Municipal Accountant on a regular basis.

We have recommended that management –
• Conduct Information/Education Campaign (IEC) within the municipality, including the barangays and schools, regarding the gains of complying with environmental laws;
• Enact ordinances and executive orders for the segregation of solid wastes at source, enforce its implementation and impose penalties to violators;
• Promote re-use and recycling of waste materials to reduce the volume of garbage to be collected and construct Materials Recovery Facilities (MRF);
• Close the open dump site, as required, and thereafter dispose waste in accordance with the guidelines set by law;
• Activate the Municipal Solid Waste Management Board (MSWB) and encourage participation of non-government organizations on the conservation of the environment; and
• Implement strictly the Tinoc Ecological Solid Waste Management Plan, if approved.

